#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.75"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.75:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 8. Arahattavagga → arahantavaggo (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.75:0.2"
msgid "8. Arahattavagga"
msgstr "8. Perfection"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.75:0.3"
msgid "75. Dukkhasutta"
msgstr "75. Suffering"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.75:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Chahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhaṃ "
"viharati savighātaṃ saupāyāsaṃ sapariḷāhaṃ, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"duggati pāṭikaṅkhā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when a mendicant has six qualities they live unhappily in the "
"present life—with distress, anguish, and fever—and when the body breaks up, "
"after death, they can expect a bad rebirth."

msgctxt "an6.75:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi chahi?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.75:1.3"
msgid ""
"Kāmavitakkena, byāpādavitakkena, vihiṃsāvitakkena, kāmasaññāya, "
"byāpādasaññāya, vihiṃsāsaññāya—"
msgstr "Sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts and perceptions."

msgctxt "an6.75:1.4"
msgid ""
"imehi, kho, bhikkhave, chahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme "
"dukkhaṃ viharati savighātaṃ saupāyāsaṃ sapariḷāhaṃ, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant has these six qualities they live unhappily in the present "
"life—with distress, anguish, and fever—and when the body breaks up, after "
"death, they can expect a bad rebirth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.75:2.1"
msgid ""
"Chahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme sukhaṃ "
"viharati avighātaṃ anupāyāsaṃ apariḷāhaṃ, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugati "
"pāṭikaṅkhā."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant has six qualities they live happily in the present life—"
"without distress, anguish, or fever—and when the body breaks up, after "
"death, they can expect a good rebirth."

msgctxt "an6.75:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi chahi?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.75:2.3"
msgid ""
"Nekkhammavitakkena, abyāpādavitakkena, avihiṃsāvitakkena, nekkhammasaññāya, "
"abyāpādasaññāya, avihiṃsāsaññāya—"
msgstr ""
"Thoughts of renunciation, love, and kindness. And perceptions of "
"renunciation, love, and kindness."

msgctxt "an6.75:2.4"
msgid ""
"imehi, kho, bhikkhave, chahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sukhaṃ viharati avighātaṃ anupāyāsaṃ apariḷāhaṃ, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"sugati pāṭikaṅkhā”ti."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant has these six qualities they live happily in the present "
"life—without distress, anguish, or fever—and when the body breaks up, after "
"death, they can expect a good rebirth.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.75:2.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
